{"type":"user.message","data":{"content":"I'm building a photo viewer page in my .NET MAUI app targeting .NET 10. I want\nthe image to fill the entire screen edge-to-edge, going behind the status bar\nand navigation bar. But my image still has padding around it even though I set\nSafeAreaEdges=\"None\" on the ContentPage. What am I missing?\n","transformedContent":"<current_datetime>2026-05-05T01:06:44.641Z</current_datetime>\n\nI'm building a photo viewer page in my .NET MAUI app targeting .NET 10. I want\nthe image to fill the entire screen edge-to-edge, going behind the status bar\nand navigation bar. But my image still has padding around it even though I set\nSafeAreaEdges=\"None\" on the ContentPage. What am I missing?","attachments":[],"interactionId":"3ce439ab-de87-47de-aabb-16c9a8c8ae61"},"id":"52a00f67-cb1f-4c4d-bb65-3323816c1b7b","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:06:44.641Z","parentId":"ff621437-d9cb-44b9-91b5-3b29cdd316f1"}
